polypeptide.name: HTH-type transcriptional regulator QacR
polypeptide.general-function: Transcription factor activity, sequence-specific dna binding
polypeptide.specific-function: Transcriptional repressor of qacA. Binds to IR1, an unusually long 28 bp operator, which is located downstream from the qacA promoter and overlaps its transcription start site. QacR is induced from its IR1 site by binding to one of many structurally dissimilar cationic lipophilic compounds, which are also substrates of QacA (By similarity).

go-classifier.description: transcription factor activity, sequence-specific DNA binding

polypeptide.name: Multidrug efflux pump subunit AcrB
polypeptide.specific-function: AcrA-AcrB-AcrZ-TolC is a drug efflux protein complex with broad substrate specificity that uses the proton motive force to export substrates.Involved in contact-dependent growth inhibition (CDI), acts downstream of BamA, the receptor for CDI. Its role in CDI is independent of the AcrA-AcrB-TolC efflux pump complex.

synonyms.synonym: AcrAB-TolC multidrug efflux pump subunit AcrB

polypeptide.name: Multidrug resistance-associated protein 1
polypeptide.specific-function: Mediates export of organic anions and drugs from the cytoplasm. Mediates ATP-dependent transport of glutathione and glutathione conjugates, leukotriene C4, estradiol-17-beta-o-glucuronide, methotrexate, antiviral drugs and other xenobiotics. Confers resistance to anticancer drugs. Hydrolyzes ATP with low efficiency.

go-classifier.description: ATPase activity, coupled to transmembrane movement of substances
